Former minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode, has claimed that Atiku Abubakar, the presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), is sweeping votes in the South West, South South, South East and North Central zones of the country. Writing on his verified Twitter page Saturday evening, Fani-Kayode stated that he was “cautiously optimistic” that Atiku will be declared Nigeria’s next president. He also advised the incumbent, President Muhammadu Buhari, to start packing his bags. “Things are looking good as @atiku appears to be sweeping the SW, SS, SE and NC. “We are on course and I am cautiously optimistic that @atiku will be declared the President-elect of the Federal Republic of Nigeria in a matter of days. “I advise @MBuhari to start packing his bags!” Fani-Kayode posted.    @realFFK Things are looking good as @atiku appears to be sweeping the SW, SS, SE and NC. We are on course and I am cautiously optimistic that @atiku will be declared the President-elect of the Federal Republic of Nigeria in a matter of days. I advise @MBuhari to start packing his bags! 1,655